---
import { ErrorDemo } from '../../components/FieldDemo';
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { meta } from './_meta/error-summary';
---

<DocsLayout title={meta.label} description={meta.description}>
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Error summary</h1>
        <p>Use an error summary at the top of a page when validation fails. Each item links to the field that needs attention.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Copy rule</h2>
        <p>Error messages should say what went wrong and how to fix it. Groundwork models error copy as structured <code class="gw-mono">FieldError</code> data: <code class="gw-mono">problem</code> names the issue and <code class="gw-mono">fix</code> gives the next action.</p>
        <p>Use <code class="gw-mono">formatFieldError</code> when custom validation UI needs the same combined copy as Field and ErrorSummary.</p>
      </div>

      <section class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Demo</h2>
        <ErrorDemo />
      </section>

      <section class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Accessibility notes</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Render the summary when validation fails and move focus to it so keyboard and screen-reader users hear the problem before returning to the form.</p>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Each summary link should point to the field that needs attention. Field-level errors still need to appear next to the relevant control; the summary does not replace inline error copy.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
